        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 4:56PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 456 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Truckton, or 29 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Truckton and Rush.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
